list.name: Default
list.comment: v0.8.0 + refact a few lines of code + fix a underlying bug "if (last != -1) consensus.addCount(inserted + i, '-')" + base counting clustering -> Quality Score clustering - in E.coli real dataset subset 10M reads - Deep Gain 0.67914003 -> 0.8412564 - Broadth Gain 0.0047826087 -> 0.012608696 + fix sliding in last update, which make unmapped segment at head/tail

task.summary: v0.1.4 + add experimental reportAll in phase 2
v0.2 + use kwartile's connected Component module instead of merging test with Ecoli dataset: TP: 886691 / 891608 FP: 1112 (260 from indel)

v0.3 + report all columns instead of inconsistent columns only # idendified bugs in kwartile's connected Component + implemented MapReduce-based connected component in 30 lines test with Ecoli dataset: recall: 887501 / 891608 fp: 583 (359 from indel) # keep all original codes, but will remove in following version

v0.3 + report all columns instead of inconsistent columns only # idendified bugs in kwartile's connected Component + implemented MapReduce-based connected component in 30 lines test with Ecoli dataset: recall: 887501 / 891608 fp: 583 (359 from indel) # keep all original codes, but will remove in following version

v0.3.1 (amend) + report all columns instead of inconsistent columns only # idendified bugs in kwartile's connected Component + implemented MapReduce-based connected component in 30 lines test with Ecoli dataset: recall: 887501 / 891608 fp: 583 (359 from indel) # keep all original codes, but will remove in following version

v0.3.2 + removed experimental codes + move out my MapReduce connected component from kwartile's code file + use All-to-min to convert List[Long] to (Long,Long) instead of All-to-All in kwartile's implementation. This slightly reduce accuracy but also reduce intermediate output 9.6G->3.2G # current E.coli dataset: 6.5min recall: 887485 / 891608 fp: 577 (356 from indel)

v0.4.0 (experimental)
+ Suffix tree + Needleman-Wunsch + LCS alignment

v0.4.1 (experimental)
+ moved to spark 2.2.0 + fix bugs 1. increase counter for non'-' gap within alignment part 2. use compact length filter 3. add variable "inserted" for '-' before alignment part 4. revise base encoding, use normal multiply for better workload balance 5. use smaller MAX_INDEL=2 6. for debug print, don't print alignment with no output

v0.4.2 + apply NW aligner for head/tail unmapped part
E.coli: recall: 887613 / 891608 fp: 342 (78 from indel)

v0.5.3 (experimental)
+ pileup by plus and minus strand, instead of individual

v0.6b
+ break pair-end to single read + change criteria: quality score sum < 60
recall: 890333 / 891608 fp: 731 (101 from indel)

v0.7
+ break pair-end to single read + change criteria: quality score sum < 60 + column separation by UnionFindSet + Fix bugs in SuffixTre + fastq file inputFormat
8.7 min Error Statistics: 891608 + 167 True Positive : 890636 + 96 False Positive : 592 (136 from indel read)

v0.7.2
+ FastqInputFormat bug fix * empty line has no line.charAt(0) == '+' * drop first fastq record whatever it's chopped or complete to avoid duplicate * String -> StringBuilder + dispatch read by network, as reload from filesystem also require network + sort reads in group by (pos,id) to unify ordering + set log level as "warn" + reportAllEdgesTuple: align by min kmer with all previous reads -> only last read
6.2 min (20 nodes, not 10 nodes) Error Statistics: 891608 + 167 True Positive : 890460 + 105 False Positive : 492 (128 from indel read)
